ons, and the simulation\nnaturally produces a much hotter stellar disc in M31 than in the MW. However,\nreconciling this scenario with the ages of stellar populations in satellite\ngalaxies would require that a higher fraction of stars previously formed in the\noutskirts of the progenitors ended up within the tidal debris, or that the\nMW-M31 interaction occurred at $z>1$.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 20 Apr 2022 18:00:01 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-04-25"}
