ed problem, we construct a wide class of initial data to the\nnonlinear equations, extending the previous framework of Guo-Strauss\n\\cite{GS95} and of Grenier \\cite{Gre00}, to prove the nonlinear Rayleigh-Taylor\ninstability in a high regime of viscosity coefficient, namely $\\mu >3\\sup_{k\\in\nL^{-1}\\mathbb{Z}\\setminus\\{0\\}}\\mu_c(k,\\Xi)$.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 21 Apr 2022 02:58:46 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 28 Apr 2022 01:45:11 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Mon, 10 Oct 2022 09:44:16 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-10-11"}
